Discarded scores are Results Thanks to coordinator Kevin Winterfield, all of the amazing volunteers, and all the riders who made this the perfect ending to an excellent year of Low-Key Hillclimbs! Bonus "epic" points to Dave Russow, who additionally rode the Hamilton backside and Quimby, and to Matt Redmond, who was late to the start due to having bicycled there from San Francisco, but still did the climb. On the team side, it's no surprise to see The Brown Zone taking the top score for the week, followed by Bike Trip and then series first overall Sisters and Misters. Local San Jose Bike Club was fourth. In the men's division, it was a Brown Zone 1-3 as Eric Wohlberg finished in less then 1:12 and Rich Brown was third not more than a minute later. Stefano Profumo of Bike Trip was second. Series leader David Collet was 8th, good enough to retain the Low-Key overall lead he took with his fantastic ride last week on Montara. In the women's division, it was a fantastic turn-out, with Lisa Penzel of Brown Zone wrapping up the women's overall finishing first here.
